=== Etymology ===
The surname is from {{Sw.}} [[Johansson]] "son of [[John]] (or ''[[Johan]]'')".  The spelling '''Johnson''' is an anglicization, adopted by, amongst others, Scandanavian immigrants to the [[United States]].  The place name is derived from the surname, the places being named after people with the family name.
